gomodel:SYNGO_3922  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In dendrites (c and d), Thr-389-P p70S6K was present in a subset of dendritic spines as revealed by double labeling for actin filaments.\nThe authors speculate the morphology of Thr-389-P p70S6K-immunoreactive puncta in dendritic shafts was similar to the morphology of hotspots of dendritic translation demonstrated in other papers in similarly cultured primary hippocampal neurons.. Experimental description: hippocampal neurons were prepared from E18 Sprague-Dawley rat embryos." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9848-0262" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4419-210X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1190-4481" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2094-7491" ;
        dc:date           "2018-09-19" ;
